Shen Haixiong, president of the China Media Group (CMG), delivered a keynote speech at the opening ceremony of the International Forum on Democracy: the Shared Human Values that took place in Beijing on Saturday. Recalling his 30-year experience as a journalist, Shen said he witnessed that the whole-process people's democracy giving the Chinese people a sense of happiness and fulfillment. China's democracy has helped 1.4 billion people get rid of absolute poverty and brought the COVID-19 pandemic under control, Shen added. Shen pointed out that international media should take greater responsibility as the world is currently undergoing unprecedented changes. "We believe in the power of justice, and we'll be committed to spreading objective and fair democratic awareness and building an ecosystem of positive and healthy global public opinion," Shen said.